Building from source
---------------

Currently, LogicBlox is required to build from source (s3lib uses jar
files from there). Before building from source, also download
additional jar dependencies using:

  $ ./download-deps

The binary distribution of s3lib is self-contained.

To build and install:

  $ ./configure
  $ make install

The default installation prefix is '/opt/logicblox/s3lib'. To
configure this, use the --prefix option. For example:

  $ ./configure --prefix=$HOME/s3lib

Usage
---------------

Generate a key and put it in the default key directory:

  $ s3lib-keygen martin
  $ mkdir -p ~/.s3lib-keys
  $ mv martin.pem ~/.s3lib-keys

Upload:

  $ cloud-store upload s3://bucket/AS400.jpg -i AS400.jpg --key martin

Download:

  $ cloud-store download s3://bucket/AS400.jpg -o AS400-2.jpg

Before you can run the cloud-store command, you need to set the environment variables AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID and AWS_SECRET_KEY to the corresponding values from your AWS credentials.

